  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nplease refer here: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/issues/25766\r\n\r\nI find the \"safe block number\" is significantly behind \"the latest block number\", and \"finalized block number\" too.\r\n\r\nIt is different with the blob: https://blog.ethereum.org/2021/11/29/how-the-merge-impacts-app-layer\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9280285/190398184-0520572f-aec3-4062-81dc-08cc6649d4c6.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nI am not sure it has the problem before The-Merge, I just use geth to get the info now.\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\nin geth console, use these commands.\r\n```\r\neth.getBlock(\"safe\").number - eth.getBlock(\"finalized\").number\r\n\r\neth.getBlock(\"latest\").number - eth.getBlock(\"safe\").number\r\n```\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\nseems the confirmed block number should >= 80 ?\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9280285/190397968-561aa2e0-8172-4ef4-94c3-62ace0fe33b6.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## üåç  Your Environment\r\n\r\n**Operating System:**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nLinux, in docker, used official docker image(ethereum/client-go:v1.10.23 and gcr.io/prysmaticlabs/prysm/beacon-chain:v3.1.1)\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n  <code>\r\nGeth version: v1.10.23\r\nprysm version: v3.1.1\r\n  </code>\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n**Anything else relevant (validator index / public key)?**\r\nNo.\r\n",
